The paper proposes a novel machine learning algorithm for data stream analytics, specifically a type of neural network called the parsimonious random vector functional link network (pRVFLN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the network's ability to select and deselect input attributes, which suggests a focus on feature selection and dimensionality reduction, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper includes simulations with real-world data streams, indicating a potential application in computer vision, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
